A pedestrian in his 70s was seriously injured after being hit by a car.
It happened near the entrance to a BP garage on Great North Road in St Neots on Sunday afternoon.
Cambridgeshire Police said a blue Ford Focus turned right into the garage in Eaton Socon at about 12:25 GMT, and hit the man.
The victim remains in a serious but stable condition in hospital, and the car driver, a man in his 30s, is assisting police with their inquiries.
Officers have appealed to anyone who witnessed the incident, or who may have dashcam footage, to get in touch.
